        </div>
        
        <div class="faq-accordion">
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-toggle">Who are the advisors on same Path?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
            <div class="faq-content">
              <p>Our advisors are heavily vetted professionals—including lawyers, recruiters, and financial planners—who specialize in immigrant and expat cases.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-toggle">How does the matching process work?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
            <div class="faq-content">
              <p>You take a brief intake quiz detailing your situation. Our system instantly matches you with the 3 most qualified advisors for your exact needs.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-toggle">Do you offer one-time sessions?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
            <div class="faq-content">
              <p>Yes. You can book a single consulting session to get immediate answers, or opt for ongoing mentorship if you need continuous guidance.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-toggle">What is the difference between a Peer Guide and an Accredited Advisor?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
            <div class="faq-content">
              <p>Peer Guides are immigrants who have successfully navigated the system and offer practical, lived-experience advice. Accredited Advisors are licensed professionals (like attorneys or CPAs) who provide legal or financial counsel.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

